Function Reference/get default post to edit « WordPress Codex
-----------

Default post information to use when populating the "Write Post" form.

Usage
-----

` <?php get_default_post_to_edit( $post_type, $create_in_db ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$post_type` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) A post type string, defaults to 'post'.
    Default: post

 `$create_in_db` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*)
    Default: false

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(object)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   stdClass object containing all the default post data as attributes

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.0](/Version_2.0 "Version 2.0")

Source File
-----------

`get_default_post_to_edit()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/post.php`

